
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `c89-gcc` baraye tabdil kardan (compile) code-haye zaban C, ke ba standard C89 neveshte shodeand, be barnameye ejraee (executable) estefade mishavad. In dastoor version ghadimi-tari az zaban C ra hemayat mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `c89-gcc -o [esme-barname] [esme-file.c]` --> 📝 Tabdil file `.c` be barnameye ejraee ba esme moshakhas.
    🔹 `c89-gcc -Wall [esme-file.c]` --> ⚠️ Namayesh hameye khatar-ha va etela'at ehtemali dar code.
    🔹 `c89-gcc -g [esme-file.c]` --> 🐛 Ezafe kardane etela'at debug baraye eslahe asan-tar.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ c89-gcc -o barname main.c

    🔹 Tabdil file `main.c` be barnameye ejraee ba esme `barname`.

    $ c89-gcc -Wall main.c

    🔹 Tabdil file `main.c` va namayesh hameye khatar-ha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ c89-gcc -o hello hello.c
    $ ./hello

    🔹 Aval code `hello.c` tabdil mishe, bad barnameye ejraee `hello` ejra mishe va natije chap mishe.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `c89-gcc` command is used to compile C language code, written according to the C89 standard, into an executable program. This command supports an older version of the C language.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `c89-gcc -o [program-name] [file-name.c]` --> 📝 Compile the `.c` file into an executable program with a specific name.
    🔹 `c89-gcc -Wall [file-name.c]` --> ⚠️ Display all warnings and potential issues in the code.
    🔹 `c89-gcc -g [file-name.c]` --> 🐛 Add debugging information for easier debugging.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ c89-gcc -o program main.c

    🔹 Compile the `main.c` file into an executable program named `program`.

    $ c89-gcc -Wall main.c

    🔹 Compile the `main.c` file and display all warnings.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ c89-gcc -o hello hello.c
    $ ./hello

    🔹 First, the `hello.c` code is compiled, then the executable program `hello` is run, and the result is printed.
